ENFLASH 0.4 README
09/08/2005


DESCRIPTION
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
EnFlash is an open source ActionScript Application Framework that 
consists of visual components, utility classes and data structures that 
enhance user experience and ease the development of sophistecated 
applications.


REQUIREMENTS
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
Macromedia Flash MX2004 or MTASC 1.6+/sfwmill 2.8+/Ant 1.6+


USAGE
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
The EnFlash package has the following structure:
/ - Contains info files, licence and a build file.
/deploy - Contains the files that are typically uploaded on a webserver.
/deploy/assets - Contains common shared assets.
/deploy/demos - Contains the current set of demos and related files.
/deploy/remoting - Contains sample AMFPHP and OpenAMF WebServices. 
/deploy/themes - Contains the graphic themes of EnFlash.
/docs - Contains javadoc like reference for EnFlash development.
/src - Contains all the source files like AS,FLA and SWFML.
/src/classes - Contains the ActionScript code of EnFlash core and demos. 
/src/flas - Contains the sources used with Macromedia Flash or swfmill.
/src/flas/assets - Contains the common assets sources. 
/src/flas/demos - Contains demos sources.
/src/flas/themes - Contains graphic themes sources.
/src/remoting - Contains remoting related sources.

In case you're using Macromedia Flash you can open and compile the demos 
using one of the FLA files provided in /src/flas/demos.

If you want to utilize the open source tools you will need to download
all of them and add them to your systems's PATH variable that will make
them accessible from everywhere. You can them compile the demos simply
by typing 'ant' in the root folder of your EnFlash package.

In order to compile the AMFDemo you will need:

Macromedia Flash Remoting Components ActionScript2 freely available at:
http://download.macromedia.com/pub/flashremoting/mx2004/components/
actionscript_2.0/flashremoting_comp_sourcecode.zip 

Update the Remoting components in order to make them compatible with
MTASC by following these steps:
http://www.swapdepths.nl/2005/06/20/get-amfphp-going-with-fame



